## 4. Database Structure — Where Your Data Lives

Your database is hosted on **Supabase** (think of it as a managed PostgreSQL database with built-in authentication). Based on the code, here's the inferred schema:

### `profiles` table — One row per user

| Column | Type | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| `id` | UUID | Matches Supabase Auth user ID |
| `email` | Text | User's email |
| `username` | Text (unique) | Global identifier like `@johndoe` |
| `full_name` | Text | Display name |
| `avatar_url` | Text | Profile picture URL |
| `plan` | Text | `FREE`, `PLUS`, `CREATOR`, or `CREATOR_PLUS` |
| `instagram` | Text | Social link (Creator only) |
| `twitter` | Text | Social link (Creator only) |
| `youtube` | Text | Social link (Creator only) |
| `website` | Text | Social link (Creator only) |
| `is_public_profile` | Boolean | Whether profile is publicly discoverable |
| `created_at` | Timestamp | When the account was created |

### `prompts` table — One row per saved prompt

| Column | Type | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| `id` | UUID | Unique prompt identifier |
| `name` | Text | Prompt title |
| `body` | Text | The actual prompt content |
| `tags` | Text[] (Array) | Category tags for filtering |
| `created_by` | UUID (FK → profiles.id) | Who owns this prompt |
| `is_public` | Boolean | Whether it appears on the public vault |
| `usage_count` | Integer | How many times the prompt was copied |
| `source_prompt_id` | UUID (nullable) | If this prompt was cloned from someone else's |
| `attribution_username` | Text (nullable) | Original creator's username for attribution |
| `created_at` | Timestamp | When the prompt was created |

### `avatars` storage bucket — Profile pictures

Files are stored as `{user_id}.webp` in Supabase Storage. Images are converted to WebP format client-side before upload for optimization.

