## 5. API Interactions — How the App Talks to the Database

There is **no traditional backend server** (no Express, no Next.js API routes). Your app talks **directly** from the browser to Supabase using the Supabase JavaScript client library. This is a "serverless" architecture.

### Communication Pattern

```
User Action → React Component → Service Function → Supabase Client → PostgreSQL Database
                                                  → Supabase Auth
                                                  → Supabase Storage
```

### Service Files — The Messengers

| Service | File | Responsibilities |
|---------|------|-----------------|
| **authService** | [authService.js](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/services/authService.js) | `signup`, `login`, `loginWithGoogle`, `ensureProfile`, `getCurrentUser`, `logout`, `updateUsername`, `updateProfile`, `getProfileByUsername` |
| **promptService** | [promptService.js](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/services/promptService.js) | `createPrompt`, `getUserPrompts`, `deletePrompt`, `incrementUsage`, `searchPrompts`, `getPublicPromptsByUserId`, `addPromptToVault` |
| **storageService** | [storageService.js](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/services/storageService.js) | Legacy localStorage-based data persistence *(no longer used by active features)* |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Dual Data Layer**: `promptService.js` contains **two separate systems** in one file. The top half (lines 1-116) is a legacy `localStorage`-based system using `storageService`. The bottom half (lines 118-305) is the live **Supabase-backed** system. The UI currently uses the Supabase functions — the legacy code is dormant but still present.

