## 7. Architectural Audit

### Where is business logic located?

| Business Logic | Location | Notes |
|------------|----------|-------|
| **Plan permission rules** | [plans.js](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/lib/plans.js) | ✅ Cleanly centralized. Single source of truth. |
| **Authentication flow** | [AuthContext.jsx](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/lib/AuthContext.jsx) | Core auth orchestration — session checking, profile merging, redirects |
| **Profile creation ("ensure")** | [authService.js](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/services/authService.js) | Auto-creates profile on first login, handles avatar defaults |
| **Prompt CRUD** | [promptService.js](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/services/promptService.js) | All database operations for prompts |
| **Duplicate detection** | [promptService.js](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/services/promptService.js) `addPromptToVault` | Prevents adding the same prompt twice |
| **Username validation** | [Profile.jsx](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/pages/Profile.jsx) + [CompleteProfile.jsx](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/pages/CompleteProfile.jsx) | ⚠️ Duplicated across two pages |
| **Auth guards (redirect if not logged in)** | Individual pages (Landing, Admin, Profile) | ⚠️ Each page has its own `useEffect` redirect logic |
| **Optimistic delete with undo** | [Admin.jsx](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/pages/Admin.jsx) | UI-level business logic embedded in a page component |
| **Feature flag gating** | [featureFlags.js](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/config/featureFlags.js) + [PromptCard.jsx](file:///d:/CODING/prompter/src/components/PromptCard.jsx) | Simple env-var driven toggle |

---

### Which parts are cleanly separated? ✅

| Area | Why it's clean |
|------|---------------|
| **Plan system** (`plans.js` + `usePlan.js`) | Perfect separation. The rules live in one file, the React binding in another. Adding a new feature or plan is a one-line change. No business logic leaks into UI. |
| **Services layer** (`authService.js`, `promptService.js`) | All Supabase calls are isolated behind service functions. Pages never call `supabase.from(...)` directly for prompt operations — they use service wrappers. |
| **Design system** (Tailwind config + `index.css`) | CSS variables and Tailwind theme tokens are centralized, ensuring consistent look across all pages. |
| **React Query caching** | Query keys are consistent (`admin-prompts`, `landing-prompts`) and the cache is manipulated via the queryClient rather than ad-hoc state. |

---

### Which parts are tightly coupled? ⚠️

| Problem | What's going on | Impact |
|---------|----------------|--------|
| **Auth guard copy-paste** | Landing, Admin, and Profile each independently check `isLoadingAuth && !isAuthenticated` and redirect. This same pattern is written 3 times instead of being a shared wrapper or route guard. | If you change the redirect logic, you have to change it in 3 places. Easy to miss one. |
| **Username validation duplication** | The regex `^[a-z0-9_]{3,20}$` and the "check if taken" logic appears in both `Profile.jsx` (with debounce) and `CompleteProfile.jsx` (inline). | Updating the rules in one place but forgetting the other would create inconsistent behavior. |
| **PromptCard knows too much** | `PromptCard` handles clipboard copying, usage tracking, vault-adding, route detection (`/public/`, `/vault/`), auth redirection, AND selection mode. It's doing 5–6 jobs. | Hard to test, hard to modify one behavior without risking the others. |
| **Direct Supabase calls in pages** | `Profile.jsx` calls `supabase.storage` and `supabase.from('profiles')` directly (for avatar upload and username availability check), bypassing the service layer. `PublicVault.jsx` and `SharedVault.jsx` also query `supabase.from('profiles')` directly. | Inconsistent data access pattern — some pages go through services, some don't. |
| **Legacy + live data layer coexistence** | `promptService.js` still contains the old localStorage-based `promptService` object alongside the new Supabase exports. The old `storageService.js` is still imported. | Dead code confusion. A new developer would struggle to know which functions are actually used. |
| **Auth page's self-contained CSS** | `Auth.jsx` and `CompleteProfile.jsx` inject their own `<style>` tags with hardcoded pixel values and colors, completely outside the Tailwind design system. | Two styling systems in one app. Changing your theme tokens in Tailwind won't affect these pages. |

